They're super friendly and go above and beyond because you can tell they enjoy the job.. The chef knows what he's doing!! Really great business to support!!

Great food and great service! The restaurant is small with limited seating, but if you go on off times you won't have a problem getting a spot. Their lunch specials are amazing and the amount of food that you get is incredible.  We always make sure to stop there when we go to St. Louis! Updated to add that with the pandemic there no dine in option but their food is still amazing!

Great food at affordable prices,  good place to phone in your order and just pick up within a short of amount of time. Highly recommended for business professionals and college students with short lunch break.

Good as usual!!
Great customer service and appreciation. Delivered a missing order to us after they made a mistake on our carry out. Friendly staff and great food.
My first time trying, and they were decent. My hot Braised chicken could have been a bit spicier, but it was good as for flavor. Will definitely be back.

I really like the place. It's look like a small place, but at lunch time it's always crowded. Why? Because those guys (and ladies) really knows how to run that place. The amount of the dishes are huge, always hot, and served in time. Prices are totally okay.
Best Chinese food in Central West End carrying on its' predecessor's history The Fortune Cookie.

100% Will order again. Fast courteous and delicious

Very high quality Chinese takeout. Though at first I was a bit surprised at the price of my order, once I opened my box it became clear that a single combo was enough to feed two people. Their combo orders have a generous potion of entree and a huge portion of fried rice, with a Crab Rag AND an Egg Roll. It was very hot and very tasty and ready as soon as I arrived. This place seemed more upscale than the Cantonese takeout places on the northside, but was undoubtedly still a takeout place. I will return soon, but I'll probably split a combo instead.
The food was delicious. I had chicken fried rice and chicken egg rolls.
Great service and excellent food. Nailed the garlic chicken first time.
Normally the food is good I only get plan fried rice with no egg with bean sprouts and two egg rolls today my 🍚 was old lumped up and stuck together 🤮

The food was ok. You could tell the cook made my food in a rush and they didn't give me anything to eat my food with. I won't EVER eat here again and I'm going to make sure tell everyone not to order or eat food from here. So disappointed.
Was excited to order from here after a few years out of the area.  The new menu is disappointing.

I placed an order today. Was excited to receive my food and all that I got was food that was definitely not cooked to order. My chicken was gray and soggy and tasted as if it had sat in a refrigerator for a couple of days. I know what my food taste like if it’s leftovers and that’s what I felt as though I spent $40 to have today was leftovers. My lo mein noodles we’re all broken and dry . Crab Rangoon maybe had a teaspoon of cream cheese in it if that I might be being a little bit too nice when I say that much. I am extremely disappointed with the food that I received and could not believe that I paid $40 for that.
The best there is. I come regularly. Hot braised chicken combo is 🔥

One of the most humiliating experiences of my life. While waiting to be placed in a long term room at Barnes Hospital I called and ordered food from to be delivered. After struggling to wheel myself to the door I find the driver to have left and refusing to answer the phone. I told the gentleman that I was coming as fast as I could then called nearly 30 times only to be sent to voicemail. I had planned on spending $20+ on just two items and a healthy tip. I could care less if this sways anyone else from ordering here as I ordered food at least 5 times a week but will never spend a single cent with you again.
The service is great, the restaurant is clean and attractive and the food is always perfectly prepared.
Cheap food, good quality, lightening fast
First time trying out West End Wok and it was fantastic!  Very quick service, the food was great and the restaurant is very clean.  It was a nice find!  I'll definitely be going back!
combo plate is terrible. no seasoning no sauce

This place. I can say so many good things about this place. The menu? Affordable and the portions are fantastic. The food? 100%. I can't describe it as anything else. Everything is so flavorful. It's like someone took Chinese take out and perfected it.

Three dishes between us. Chicken and snow peas for me was super bland. Sesame chicken was tough and meat was overcooked. Similar for the other chicken dish. Good egg rolls, delicious hot and sour soup. Veggies in dishes looked fresh and tasted fine. Unlikely to go back unless just for soup.
Hmmm.  Fast.
Beef with snow peas is very good

West End Wok is the best Chinese in St. Louis. Busiest times are 12 on week days. I have had almost everything on the menu. I recommend eating it fresh. Their fresh general tso chicken is phenomenal! For what you get the price is great ! I hope nothing changes about this place. This is better than many other Chinese food even ones that are more expensive. Plus they have a buy 10 combination punch card get one free. so good !
This place is the best! Our go-to for Chinese take-out. We moved out of their delivery area and we still pick-up from here because it’s such a good deal and always tasty.
I love West end wok the food is clean and delicious.

One of my favorite restaurants in St. Louis
Good price and consistent quality. This place makes me look forward to lunch and can help turn a bad day around.
Lovely little restaurant. Food was good and the wait time was not long at all.
I had the west end beef... it was so delicious! Crispy, sweet, and tender. I have yet to find a restaurant with a comparable dish.
The best I've found in STL.

Food was ok

I've been here several times. I work nearby, so it's out "go-to" place for Chinese food. The service is fast & friendly whether eating in or getting it to go. I've had several dishes here and all have been cooked very well. The General Tso's and the Mongolian Beef are my favorites, but you can go wrong with the Sesame Chicken. The soups are the best, so get the combo. The fried rice is delicious. The egg rolls and crab rangoon could be larger, but you get two with each combo which is a lot of food.

I love the food, but have had bad experiences with delivery. Ordered just now, and the delivery person, was a special type of individual, impolite and rude,   didn't even respond when I said  good evening.
Really good food. Picked up some GT chicken. Was well done, and the extras were good too. Will come back for sure.
Good food good people large proshens.
The service here is usually quick and friendly. Their chicken lo mein is really good. It is a bit cramped inside especially  around lunch time.
Small restaurant. Food was amazing. The best Chinese food I have ever eaten. Unfortunately the service was subpar.
One of my faves Chinese restaurant to go to!
Great food, friendly service!! Win, win!!
Always a great lunch with the combination plate! Fresh and tasty!
This place rocks. Best Chinese food in town .
Had the beef fried rice. Very good. Also the crab Rangoon was very good. Was in town for vacation and will definitely eat here again if I'm in St Louis.
Super cute waitress
Good service and good food. Nice people.

Nothing less than Amazingly Delicious... They are always so friendly, attentive & patient!😄 They are always so accurate when we ask for our food made a specific way.... The vegetable lo mein is by far one of the best in st. Louis... Their pot stickers are out of this world including the homemade sauce that comes with them... And the Green Bean Chicken is off of the charts... Love this place, a must try! Gauranteed you wont stop going back!
Fast, friendly, good food and a lot of food for the price.

Wow just wow! I don't know if it was the chef, the recipe or both but my meal was so bland and unsatisfying. Big portions? Yes, but I'll take a great tasting meal over a large one any day. You may have better luck but definitely not with the Kung Pao beef.

Service was very good, and at a good price, with great food! If you are looking to try something new, or just want to eat out, West End Wok is a great choice, anytime. I would recommend the spicy beef or curry chicken.

Decided to try this place out, Being the reviews were great and it was close to home... got the food quick and it was a good price... little over priced for the portion sizes but it was decent priced.  Got the food, it was cold... and the food itself tasted so bland... no seasoning, spice or anything what so ever.  Felt cheated out of my money... but hey, at least I know where not to stop next time.
Fast, cheap and fantastic quality. I don't think I've ever gotten Chinese this good for less than $10.
Fastest lunch ever. But more important delicious food. Very reasonable prices too. Highly recommend.
Great price, great food! Very fast service and wish I lived closer so I could enjoy it more often!

I will never comeback to this place and will certainly tell all my family and friends about this - not worth it I hope the owners of this place know what kind of employee have working for them. Fast service, fair prices.

The spicy chicken was just ok as was the Mongolian beef. The West End Beef, however, was fantastic and is a favorite of our friends who live in St. Louis.  The crab rangoons are very nice and are a good size with a good amount of filling. The egg drop soup can be skipped and I've heard the hot and sour soup is much better.
Excellent!!! Just ate here with my dad. Food was great! General chicken was amazing! Will come back!
What a great place. The food is consistently tasty and well prepared. The portions are a great value.  Under $10 for a great Chinese dinner and soup.

Food marked spicy was so extremely spicy that I could not eat the entree, only the rice, eggroll and crab ragoon which were excellent. I have eaten Chinese food marked spicy at many restaurants and have eaten it with no problem.

super quick. lunch specials  are great.

When you're craving that greasy spring roll and fried rice, this is the spot to go to. Very inexpensive, quality is good but not great. But, I still find myself going every other week! Gotta get the combo- they let you substitute things in the combo, ie. you can get 3 crab rangoons instead of the spring roll and soup.

Best hot sour soup I have ever tasted (I might be slightly addicted), good egg rolls, amazing pot stickers, good crab Rangoon, and just tried the sesame chicken with white rice combo. Good portions, very good chicken...I love it!

Food is incredible but the service is very poor. It's sad because they could be an awesome restaurant but the people who pick up the phone are terribly rude.

Food very good and delivery was quick.  The negative is that in the days of internet ordering they are not updating their website menu or honoring their advertised prices.  He charged me and extra $5 for my 2 meals.  The other issue is they only advertise 1 price (lower $) which is the partial order vice the full order meals.  Lastly, the full size order combination on their website doesn't include the extras like soups etc that it clearly states comes with the plates.  To me they are bringing you in with misleading prices and then tacking on extra costs while saying "no" they won't honor their own website.
So far the best chinese food that I have had in St. Louis.

Picture the perfectly decent Chinese food delivery you have in mind.  This is it.  The food has always been good, the staff are nice, and the delivery time is bizarrely fast.  Sometimes they arrive before you hang up the phone!  It's one of the best delivery options in the area that is consistently pleasant.  You get a lot of food for the price too, especially with the combos.  I'm not affiliated with the restaurant.
The best thing about this place is the large portions for a good price.  My favorite chinese restaurant in the area!
good food. fast service.
Very quick and tasty!  Crab rangoon and eggrolls are perfect!
High quality ingredients, generous portions, reasonable prices.
Ordered the Hot Braised Chicken, Best is St.Louis hands down.. Crab ragoon good also
Awesomeshrimp fried rice
The best sesame chicken I have had from a Chinese restaurant. Clean place, definitely one of the better Chinese restaurants I have been to, and I am a fan of Chinese food. I recommend it.

I wish they were open on Sundays. Because West End Wok was closed tonight, we ordered from another Chinese restaurant in the area. This will not happen again. The food from West End Wok is so much better that it reveals the awfulness of other Chinese restaurants in the area.  I can't specifically identify what they are doing that makes their food better, maybe the ingredients they use at West End are simply fresher, but regardless of the reason for their superior quality, West End is the best generic, reasonably priced, American style, Chinese food in the metro area.
